l, Kinnerley, Shropshire, England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","of Caehowel,Kinnerley,Shropshire,England":"Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]},{"name":"verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Matilda verch Ieuan was born about 1154, in Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Iowerth Goch ap Gryffin Goch, was 36 and her mother, Mrs- IOWERTH \" Goch\" ap Griffith, was 31. She married Gruffudd de Sutton ap Gervase Coch about 1189, in Kinnerley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"Abt 1154–":"umbes 1154–Surnud","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1150–1221":"1150–1221","1190–1280":"1190–1280